members.name: Whanau Meats
members.description: We are a family owned and family values driven business run by father-daughter duo. We have returned to our ancestral home in Te Hiku, the Far North, to reconnect and to provide the best in service and produce to our local community through Whānau Meats, a butchery and homekill processor. At Whānau Meats we aim to be the best at what we do: provide delicious meat and home kill processing that is cost-effective and a place where you/’ll enjoy being part of a whānau (family) atmosphere.

members.name: Dune Rider Tours
members.description: Dune Rider Unique Tours is the name of our family-owned and operated tour company with over 20 years of experience. We work together as a team to provide you with the best experiences the Far North has to offer.

members.name: Harrisons Cape Runner
members.description: Relax and unwind as our local tour guides take you on a journey to share with you some of our amazing Maori legends and Far North history.

members.description: We have always been recognised for a willingness to get alongside our clients. We like business development and helping out with our clients business management needs.

members.name: KCL Civil Construction
members.description: With over 15 years Civil Construction experience, we understand how challenging this specialist area can be. Centrally located in the Far North, we offer a full range of support from consultation and project management, to the physical completion of the project.
